23:["$","li",null,{"className":"x:my-[.5em]","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Static automation"}],": Cron jobs run whether needed or not. The World Engine only acts when a goal deviation is detected."]}]
24:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":["The key invariant is: ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"goals are declared, not coded"}],". What “healthy” means lives in ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"goals.yaml"}],", not in business logic. This means goal definitions can evolve without touching the planner."]}]
25:["$","hr",null,{"className":"x:my-[2em] nextra-border"}]
26:["$","h2",null,{"id":"htngoap-hybrid-how-action-planning-works","className":"x:tracking-tight x:text-slate-900 x:dark:text-slate-100 x:font-semibold x:target:animate-[fade-in_1.5s] x:mt-10 x:border-b x:pb-1 x:text-3xl nextra-border","children":["HTN/GOAP hybrid: how action planning works",["$","$L22",null,{"id":"htngoap-hybrid-how-action-planning-works"}]]}]
27:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"The World Engine combines two planning paradigms:"}]
28:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Goal-Oriented Action Planning (GOAP)"}]," defines what the system is trying to achieve. A goal is a predicate on world state — a function that returns ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"true"}]," when the system is in the desired condition. The planner’s job is to find a sequence of actions that transforms current state into a state where the goal predicate returns ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"true"}],"."]}]
29:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Hierarchical Task Networks (HTN)"}]," decompose abstract intentions into concrete actions. A portfolio-level objective (“improve system stability”) decomposes into project-level tasks (“fix auth service”) which decompose into domain-level operations (“restart auth”, “roll back config”) which finally reach primitive actions (“call restart API endpoint”)."]}]
2a:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"The hierarchy has four levels:"}]
2b:["$","div",null,{"data-pagefind-ignore":"all","className":"nextra-code x:relative x:not-first:mt-[1.25em]","children":["$undefined",["$","pre",null,{"className":"x:group x:focus-visible:nextra-focus x:overflow-x-auto x:subpixel-antialiased x:text-[.9em] x:bg-white x:dark:bg-black x:py-4 x:ring-1 x:ring-inset x:ring-gray-300 x:dark:ring-neutral-700 x:contrast-more:ring-gray-900 x:contrast-more:dark:ring-gray-50 x:contrast-more:contrast-150 x:rounded-md not-prose","tabIndex":"0","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"x:group-hover:opacity-100 x:group-focus:opacity-100 x:opacity-0 x:transition x:focus-within:opacity-100 x:flex x:gap-1 x:absolute x:right-4 x:top-2","children":[["$","$L5a",null,{"children":["$","svg",null,{"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"currentColor","height":"1em","children":["$","path",null,{"d":"M4 19h6v-2H4v2zM20 5H4v2h16V5zm-3 6H4v2h13.25c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2s-.9 2-2 2H15v-2l-3 3l3 3v-2h2c2.21 0 4-1.79 4-4s-1.79-4-4-4z"}]}]}],false]}],["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"children":"portfolio  — org-wide strategic objectives"}]}],"\n",["$","span",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"children":"  └── project  — per-project tactical goals"}]}],"\n",["$","span",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"children":"        └── domain  — domain-specific operations (services, CI, board)"}]}],"\n",["$","span",null,{"children":["$","span",null,{"children":"              └── action  — primitive executable steps"}]}]]}]]}]]}]
2c:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"The two paradigms complement each other. GOAP answers “what goal are we trying to satisfy?”. HTN answers “what sequence of concrete steps gets us there?”. The planner uses HTN decomposition to generate the candidate action set, then A* search to find the least-cost path through that action graph to the goal state."}]
2d:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"In practice this means:"}]
2e:["$","ol",null,{"className":"x:[:is(ol,ul)_&]:my-[.75em] x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:list-decimal x:ms-6","children":["\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"x:my-[.5em]","children":["A goal violation is detected (",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"world.goal.violated"}]," event)"]}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"x:my-[.5em]","children":"The HTN decomposer traverses the hierarchy top-down, producing a list of applicable primitive actions"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"x:my-[.5em]","children":"The A* planner searches through possible action sequences to find the least-cost plan that satisfies the goal"}],"\n",["$","li",null,{"className":"x:my-[.5em]","children":"The plan is executed (or escalated if outside budget)"}],"\n"]}]
